Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Pat @artichoke hearts{1%unit} dry with #paper towels{}; halve crosswise. Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce} lengthwise.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels.

Lay two slices of @prosciutto{2%ounce} beside one another on a #work surface{}. Tightly roll up prosciutto around chicken. Repeat with remaining prosciutto and chicken.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%ounce}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1/2 cup pasta cooking water (1 cup for 4 servings), then drain.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add wrapped chicken and cook until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to one side of a #baking sheet{}. Wipe out pan.

Add artichoke hearts to empty side of sheet and toss with a drizzle of oil.

Roast on top rack until chicken is cooked through and artichokes are browned and slightly crispy, ~{15-18%minutes}. Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}.

== Spicy Breadcrumbs ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring constantly, until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Stir in parsley and as many @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like. Wipe out pan.

== Creamy Burst Tomato Penne ==

Once chicken and artichokes have roasted 10 minutes, heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for breadcrumbs over medium-high heat. Add tomatoes and cook, undisturbed, until browned and beginning to burst, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low. Stir in @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, drained penne, and 1/4 cup reserved pasta cooking water (1/2 cup for 4 servings). Bring to a low simmer and cook, stirring constantly, until pasta is evenly coated in sauce, ~{1-2%minutes}. (If needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time.)

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

== To Serve ==

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide pasta between #shallow bowls{}; sprinkle with spicy breadcrumbs. Top with chicken and artichokes and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.